---

<DocsLayout title="Landing page arc" description="Cleo landing page emotional arc">
  <div class="prose">
    <h1>Landing page emotional arc</h1>
    <p class="page-lead">The marketing page is not a product tour. It is Frames 1–4 in sequence.</p>

    <h2>Act 1 — Recognition (Frames 1–2)</h2>
    <p>Hero names the wound: still charting, still getting denials. No feature list above the fold.</p>

    <h2>Act 2 — Differentiation (Frames 4–6)</h2>
    <p>Headline that lands. Demo that proves. Denial prevention that no one else shows.</p>

    <h2>Act 3 — Destination (Frames 7–8)</h2>
    <p>Close with done before 5pm and home for dinner — specific, not aspirational fluff.</p>

    <PhilosophyCallout>
      <p>One amber CTA on the entire page. Everything else is slate or ghost. The page should feel like putting something down.</p>
    </PhilosophyCallout>
  </div>
</DocsLayout>
